Motherboard : The Skeleton and Nerves
RAM : Short-term Memory
PSU : Heart and lungs (power supply)
CPU : The Brains
GPU : Visual Cortex
HDD + SSD : Long-term memory
Network Adapter : Communicate with other computer and network
Input & output devices : To send and receive data
UEFI : Interface between the OS and platform firmware
BIOS : Boot firmware that provides runtime services for the OS

Processing Steps
(i) Press the power button
(ii) Firmware Starts
(iii) Power-on Self Test
(iv) Select Boot Device
(v) Initiate Bootloader
